{"id":"264907677_The_l_-medial_axis","abstract":"Medial axis is known to be unstable for nonsmooth objects. For an open set O, we define the weak feature size, wfs, minimum distance between O(c) and the critical points of the function distance to O(c). We introduce the \"lambda-medial axis\" M(lambda) of O, a subset of the medial axis of O which captures the homotopy type of O when lambda < wfs. We show that, at least for some \"regular\" values of lambda, M(lambda) remains stable under Hausdorff distance perturbations of O(c). (c) 2005 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.","authors":["Frédéric Chazal","André Lieutier"],"meta":["July 2005Graphical Models 4(4)","DOI:10.1016/j.gmod.2005.01.002"],"references":["226022599_Stability_and_Finiteness_Properties_of_Medial_Axis_and_Skeleton","225544816_Surface_Reconstruction_by_Voronoi_Filtering","221115965_Approximate_medial_axis_as_a_Voronoi_subcomplex","221115887_Efficient_Computation_of_A_Simplified_Medial_Axis","220983795_Weak_feature_size_and_persistent_homology_Computing_homology_of_solids_in_R_n_from_noisy_data_samples","220677909_Hexahedral_Mesh_Generation_using_the_Embedded_Voronoi_Graph","42741729_Stability_and_Computation_of_Medial_Axes_a_State-of-the-Art_Report","2850862_Alpha-Shapes_and_Flow_Shapes_are_Homotopy_Equivalent","2845976_Approximating_the_Medial_Axis_from_the_Voronoi_Diagram_with_a_Convergence_Guarantee","311477775_Generalized_gradients_and_applications","268617368_Algebraic_topology_A_first_course","248427578_When-boundaries_are_manifolds","247446619_Examples_of_topological_properties_of_skeletons","243078056_Generalized_Gradients_and_Applications","242571530_Critical_Point_Theory_for_Distance_Functions","242471712_Algebraic_Topology_An_Introduction","239552210_Surface_Reconstruction_by_Wrapping_Finite_Sets_in_Space","225624867_Semianalytic_and_subanalytic_sets","222623673_The_Flow_Complex_A_Data_Structure_for_Geometric_Modeling","222563547_Computing_Voronoi_skeletons_of_a_3-D_polyhedron_by_space_subdi